# GNU Stow ignore list for this package.
#
# Stow uses this file INSTEAD of its built-in default ignore list once it
# exists (it does not merge the two), so the usual defaults are replicated
# below, followed by our own additions. This replaces passing
# --ignore='^setup($|/)' on every stow invocation - see README.md.
#
# Lines with no "/" are matched against each path segment's basename.
# Lines containing "/" are matched against the full relative path.

# --- GNU Stow's own built-in defaults (kept so we don't lose them) ---
RCS
.+,v

CVS
\.\#.+       # CVS conflict files / emacs lock files
\.cvsignore

\.svn
_darcs
\.hg

\.git
\.gitignore
\.gitmodules

.+~          # emacs backup files
\#.*\#       # emacs autosave files

^/README.*
^/LICENSE.*
^/COPYING

# --- Our additions ---

# Bootstrap/setup scripts aren't dotfiles - never symlink them into $HOME
^/setup

# Claude Code local project state - not a dotfile to symlink into $HOME
^/\.claude

# Omarchy theme sources, mirroring the omarchy repo's own root-level themes/
# layout - not a dotfile itself, referenced directly by path (like
# $OMARCHY_PATH/themes) rather than symlinked into $HOME
^/themes

# Theme template fragments (colors.toml -> per-app color file), mirroring
# omarchy's own root-level default/themed/ - read directly by path, not
# a dotfile to symlink into $HOME
^/default
